defaultThe Highways Agency is responsible for the strategic road network in 
defaultEngland
default, covering more than 4,300 miles of motorways and trunk roads.  The Agency delivers a robust 
defaultwinter service that has been developed over a number of years, with significant improvements introduced following previous reviews and lessons learned.  The Agency is well prepared for winter weather.
